<TITLE> Bail granted to BNP leaders in defamation case </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 31 (bdnews24.com)  The High Court on Wednesday granted anticipatory bail to opposition chief whip Joynal Abdin Farroque and MP Shahid Uddin Chowdhury Anny in a case alleging that they had made 'derogatory remarks' about the prime minister's son Sajeeb Ahmed Wazed. The case had been filed against them in Chittagong on March 25 by advocate Dirghatomo Baruafor. The vacation bench of justice Shahidul Islam granted bail for Farroque and Anny on Wednesday. Barrister Mahbubuddin Khokon represented the two in the court. Additional attorney general MK Rahman stood for the government and opposed the plea for bail. b
